    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0001">Downing</placeName> Febr. 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1779</dateline>
                    <salute>Dear
                    Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Please to accept the promised <rs type="art" ref="ardb.xml#ar0007">print</rs>.<note type="editorial">Print not identified.</note> I am sorry I
                    cannot offer you <rs type="art" ref="ardb.xml#ar0008">that of myself</rs>:<note type="editorial">A line engraving of Thomas Pennant by John Keyse Sherwin,
                        after Thomas Gainsborough, was published on 1 January 1779. See NPG
                        D19671.</note> many reasons inducing me to make that venal. It may be had at
                        <persName ref="pe0141">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Majors</persName>
                    <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0781">St Martin's lane</placeName>
                   <note type="editorial">Thomas Major (1720–1799), engraver. In 1752 he moved to
                        Chandos Street, off lower St Martin’s lane. ODNB.</note>. I hope next winter
                    to pass some time in town; &amp; to enjoy a little of y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Company. Pray excuse the second tax I put on you by requesting the
                    inclosed may be directed to <persName ref="pe0323">P. Panton esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    </persName>
                   <note type="editorial">LINK TO BIOGRAPHIES: Paul Panton, junior</note>
                    <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0782">N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 12 Serles street
                        Lincolns inn London</placeName>. I am with much esteem</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Dear Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>obliged &amp; most
                        obedient <lb/>
                        <sic>humbl</sic> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Thomas
                    Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
